snippet.textDisplay:
Hey Filip! Thanks for making these videos, it’s cool to speculate what Apple might do. As far as your Rebel cases are concerned, I must say, someone finally made an iPhone case the way it should be!!! The main reason why I rarely use a case on my iPhone 8 Plus is because I don’t get to “feel” the phone (and because of that I’ve cracked and scratched many a phone). I hope to buy one of your cases soon. I’m sure I’ll go with the one with the magnetic attachments, but look forward to when you put the magnets in a frosted glass as the webpage says you are looking into. Just one thing, and this is the reason I decided to comment, have you heard of Polymagnets? They are so efficient!!! I would absolutely love to see you use them for your cases. That I would have to buy. The company is called Correlated Magnets, and they’re not too expensive, it seems. They can actually print magnetic fields. I found out about them through Destin at Smarter Every Day, that visited them. I would totally recommend you using those for the cases.
Anyway, thanks for taking the time to read this rather long comment!
